PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of Semiu Adeyemi Adeniran as the substantive Statistician-General of the Federation and Chief Executive Officer of the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) The appointment takes effect immediately. A statement issued and signed by the Special Assistant, Media, to the Minister of State for Budget and Planning, Sufuyan Ojeifo, said the appointment followed the demise of the former Statistician-General of the Federation, Simon Harry, on April 13, 2022. Adeniran is a professional statistician with bias for demography and social statistics. He has over three decades of statistical hands-on experience garnered from various local and international institutions, the statement said. Until his appointment, he was the Director of Demographic and Household Statistics at the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).